&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Acute Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Appointment of a Substantive Consultant in Acute Medicine with a Sub Specialty Interest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust are seeking to appoint an enthusiastic consultant to join our well established department. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;How We’ll Look After You&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will support the successful applicant to maximize their potential with a series of excellent benefits and opportunities: We will invest in your training and support you to pursue a successful and fulfilling career and encourage the development of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;your&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; sub-speciality interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generous relocation and educational support packages are available. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please contact the department for details&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a family friendly Trust we offer an onsite nursery to support our employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The AMU is situated in a purpose built ward area in close proximity to the Urgent and Emergency Care Centre (UECC) and sits within the Division of Integrated Medicine. The division of Integrated medicine is active and dynamic, with thriving collaborative working arrangements across South Yorkshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department for Acute Medicine at Rotherham Hospital comprises of:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;29 bedded Medical Admissions Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;12 bedded Short Stay Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ambulatory Care Medical Unit (12 chairs)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Frailty assessment and liaison team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent facilities are available to consultant employees, including a dedicated ultrasound machine to support teaching and acute diagnostics, a departmental seminar room and dedicated secretarial support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The department at Rotherham is home to a friendly, diverse and accommodating team who will welcome new colleagues and support them in all aspects of their role. The team shares a passion for change, growth, quality improvement and innovation in pursuing clinical excellence &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Area&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rotherham is surrounded by beautiful countryside and picturesque villages, and situated within easy access of transport links, the Peak District National Park, and major urban centres, such as Sheffield and Leeds. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Housing in the area and surrounding areas is plentiful and good value compared to the national average. Satisfactory and affordable accommodation is also available on the hospital site. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are several “outstanding” schools in the local area and coaches also run from Rotherham to several highly-regarded independent schools nearby.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An information pack detailing transport links, schools and a number of other useful local guidance can be requested from the department. We will cater this pack to individuals, with specific queries, upon request.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed, please contact: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Kishor Athavale; Consultant Physician and Director of Clinical Services for Integrated Medicine on 01709 424163 (Secretary) orEmail: Nandkishor.athavale@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ben Vasey; Deputy General Manager on 01709 424167 or Email Benjamin.Vasey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware that we will need references for the past 3 years employment. Your referees must be from your Medical Manager or Medical Director if already in a Consultant post. If they are to be requested via email it must be via an institutional email address.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
